PN,30811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773187388
OL,3,CMail Editor claims she kept Princess
OL,4,Cof Wales' pregnancy a secret for days
OL,6,FDavid Sherborne, representing the
OL,7,Fgroup of household names bringing the
OL,8,Fclaim, suggested that Griffiths had
OL,9,F"invented" her story about William
OL,10,Ftelling a group at the country weekend
OL,11,Fthat Kate was pregnant.
OL,13,FHe also proposed that Griffiths was
OL,14,F"making up" connections with the royal
OL,15,Ffamily, and she "deliberately"
OL,16,Foverplayed her relationship with Harry.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30812
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773187388
OL,3,CMail Editor claims she kept Princess
OL,4,Cof Wales' pregnancy a secret for days
OL,6,FGriffiths denied all of these claims.
OL,7,FSherborne also suggested Griffiths had
OL,8,Fused private investigators who engaged
OL,9,Fin unlawful acts to write articles in
OL,10,Fthe claim related to Sir Elton and
OL,11,FHurley.
OL,13,FThe editor said she had sources for
OL,14,Fthe information that appeared in the
OL,15,Fstories Sherborne was referencing.
OL,17,FLater in the day, the editor of the
OL,18,FMail on Sunday, David Dillon, started
OL,19,Fgiving his evidence in the case.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30813
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1773187388
OL,3,CMail Editor claims she kept Princess
OL,4,Cof Wales' pregnancy a secret for days
OL,6,FIn written submissions, Sherborne
OL,7,Falleged that Dillon had approved "many
OL,8,Finvoices for unlawful acts" and had
OL,9,Falso instructed private investigator
OL,10,FSteve Whittamore directly when he was
OL,11,Fa news editor at the paper.
OL,13,FDillon denied these claims in his
OL,14,Fwitness statement, writing, "In over
OL,15,F25 years at the Mail on Sunday, I have
OL,16,Fnever known of anyone hacking or
OL,17,Ftapping a phone, nor have I ever been
OL,18,Fasked to, asked anyone else to, or
OL,19,Fhacked or tapped a phone myself."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
